               ----------------------------------------
            FFRStatus - The Fido File Request Server V 2.30
                    (C) 1991-95 by Francis Wauquier
               ----------------------------------------

                             Cahn's Axiom:

              When all else fails, read the instructions.

     FFRS_Status is a small program waiting for a file request in the
     background. If a file request with FFRS starts, it pops up a
     window informing you about the requester's name, node, node name
     and two scollable lists  with  the filenames requested and the
     files being sent.

     Another string gadget informs you about what FFRS is currently
     doing (you'll see everything FFRS writes into its log)

     FFRS_Status operates completely asynchronously so FFRS needn't
     wait for operations being completed by FFRS_Status. After FFRS has
     completed its work, the status window will remain open for a
     configurable delay (15 seconds by default). You can also click on
     the close gadget at any time.

     FFRS_Status is an optional program - if you don't like it or if
     you want to save some memory, just don't run it.

     FFRS_Status is font sensitive.


