Operating FFRS_Status.
**********************

   @{b}*@{ub} You can start FFRS_Status either:


 @{" from Workbench " Link "from Workbench"} 
 @{" from CLI " Link "from CLI"} 


@EndNode

@Node "from Workbench" "FFRStatus.guide/from Workbench"
@Next "from CLI"
@Toc "Operation"

Using FFRS_Status from Workbench.
=================================

   Simply click on the FFRS_Status icon.


@EndNode

@Node "from CLI" "FFRStatus.guide/from CLI"
@Prev "from Workbench"
@Toc "Operation"

Using FFRS_Status from CLI.
===========================

     Example: run >nil: mail:bin/FFRS_Status

   @{b}*@{ub} The most convenient and recommended way of installation is to
     simply move FFRS_Status to your WBStartup directory.


@EndNode

