Configuration of FFRS_Status.
*****************************

   Configuration is done via Workbench ToolTypes or via commandline
parameters. They are explained in this section, some examples follow
right afterwards.The abbreviations (like PS for PUBSCREEN) may only be
used from the CLI.


 @{" PS=PUBSCREEN-K " Link "PS=PUBSCREEN-K"} 
 @{" CD=CLOSEDELAY-K-N " Link "CD=CLOSEDELAY-K-N"} 
 @{" FONT=FONTNAME-K " Link "FONT=FONTNAME-K"} 
 @{" FS=FONTSIZE-K-N " Link "FS=FONTSIZE-K-N"} 
 @{" WINX-K-N " Link "WINX-K-N"} 
 @{" WINY-K-N " Link "WINY-K-N"} 
 @{" WIDTH-K-N " Link "WIDTH-K-N"} 
 @{" HEIGHT-K-N " Link "HEIGHT-K-N"} 


@EndNode

@Node "PS=PUBSCREEN-K" "FFRStatus.guide/PS=PUBSCREEN-K"
@Next "CD=CLOSEDELAY-K-N"
@Toc "Configuration"

Using Public Screen.
====================

   @{b}*@{ub} Set the public screen where the status window should pop up.

     Example: PUBSCREEN=TrapDoor

     Default: Default public screen (usually the Workbench screen)

     Note: TrapDoor 1.83 is the first publically available version that
     supports public screens. Use "SCREENMODE PUBLIC" in your
     trapdoor.cfg if you want the FFRS status window to open on the
     TrapDoor screen.


@EndNode

@Node "CD=CLOSEDELAY-K-N" "FFRStatus.guide/CD=CLOSEDELAY-K-N"
@Next "FONT=FONTNAME-K"
@Prev "PS=PUBSCREEN-K"
@Toc "Configuration"

Close Delay after use.
======================

   @{b}*@{ub} Set the close delay for the status window after FFRS has completed
     its work.

     Example: CLOSEDELAY=25

     Default: 15 seconds


@EndNode

@Node "FONT=FONTNAME-K" "FFRStatus.guide/FONT=FONTNAME-K"
@Next "FS=FONTSIZE-K-N"
@Prev "CD=CLOSEDELAY-K-N"
@Toc "Configuration"

Changing fonts.
===============

   @{b}*@{ub} Set the font to be used. Allows even proportional fonts!

     Example: FONTNAME=myfont.fonts

     Default: default font on screen


@EndNode

@Node "FS=FONTSIZE-K-N" "FFRStatus.guide/FS=FONTSIZE-K-N"
@Next "WINX-K-N"
@Prev "FONT=FONTNAME-K"
@Toc "Configuration"

Changing fonts size.
====================

   @{b}*@{ub} Set the font size to be used.

     Example: FONTSIZE=15

     Default: default size on screen


@EndNode

@Node "WINX-K-N" "FFRStatus.guide/WINX-K-N"
@Next "WINY-K-N"
@Prev "FS=FONTSIZE-K-N"
@Toc "Configuration"

Set X windows coordinate.
=========================

   @{b}*@{ub} Status window x position

     Example: WINX=10

     Default: 0


@EndNode

@Node "WINY-K-N" "FFRStatus.guide/WINY-K-N"
@Next "WIDTH-K-N"
@Prev "WINX-K-N"
@Toc "Configuration"

Set Y windows coordinate.
=========================

   @{b}*@{ub} Status window y position

     Example: WINY=10

     Default: 0


@EndNode

@Node "WIDTH-K-N" "FFRStatus.guide/WIDTH-K-N"
@Next "HEIGHT-K-N"
@Prev "WINY-K-N"
@Toc "Configuration"

Set window with.
================

   @{b}*@{ub} Status window width.

     Example: WIDTH=100

     Default: depends on font


@EndNode

@Node "HEIGHT-K-N" "FFRStatus.guide/HEIGHT-K-N"
@Prev "WIDTH-K-N"
@Toc "Configuration"

Set window height.
==================

   @{b}*@{ub} Status window height.

     Example: HEIGHT=100

     Default: depends on font


@EndNode

